OL,3,CMaking female train driver work
OL,4,CSaturdays 'is not sex discrimination'
OL,6,FExpecting a female London Underground
OL,7,Fdriver to work on a Saturday did not
OL,8,Famount to sex discrimination, an
OL,9,Femployment judge has ruled.
OL,11,FExperienced train operator Nicola
OL,12,FJones requested every other Saturday
OL,13,Foff to look after her child, but when
OL,14,FLondon Underground told her she would
OL,15,Fhave to work them to keep up the
OL,16,Fquality of the network's service, she
OL,17,Ftook the company to an employment
OL,18,Ftribunal.
