OL,3,CMaking female train driver work
OL,4,CSaturdays 'is not sex discrimination'
OL,6,FMs Jones had been working for the
OL,7,Fcompany since 2001 and was based at
OL,8,Fthe Hainault depot in north-east
OL,9,FLondon.
OL,11,FMs Jones' child was born in 2013, and
OL,12,Fshe had avoided working on Saturdays
OL,13,Fsince then because her husband is a
OL,14,Fbus driver who is required to work
OL,15,Fevery weekend, an east London
OL,16,Femployment tribunal heard.
OL,18,FShe told bosses she needed shift
OL,19,Fpatterns that were opposite to her
OL,20,Fhusband's so their child was always
OL,21,Fcared for, the tribunal was told.
