OL,6,FThe company's "explanation for
OL,7,Frefusing Ms Jones' request to be
OL,8,Fallowed not to work on Saturdays was
OL,9,Fmotivated by a wish to avoid a queue
OL,10,Fof employees requesting alternate
OL,11,Fduties on hours which suited them.
OL,13,F"That reason is not because of sex,"
OL,14,FJudge Shore added.
OL,16,FMs Jones' claim of victimisation also
OL,17,Ffailed, but she was awarded #2,720 in
OL,18,Fcompensation because London
OL,19,FUnderground "did not act reasonably"
OL,20,Fin the way it dealt with her request,
OL,21,Fthe tribunal ruled.
